  "title": "Local Clusters, Cluster Lifecycle, Conformance, Upgrades, Backup, and Production Defense",
  "description": "An operations board must distinguish a local minikube proof from production, upgrade a supported cluster without skipped minors, recover control-plane state, and defend remaining risks. Learners cumulatively produce cluster lifecycle and recovery defense through theory, guided work, debugging, transfer, retrieval, and assessment.",
